I do pay for it, through my Satellite TV Subscription. I do not wish to buy a $300 DVR, however, nor do I want to record it on VHS. I DO, however, want to be able to watch it at my convenience.

SG-U airs in the US on SciFy (aka, the wrestling/craptacular-not-so-reality-tv-channel) on Monday. It airs in Canada on Space (A REAL Science Fiction channel) on Tuesday. I generally hold off on downloading until after it airs on Tuesday.
I'm doing nothing wrong, but using my computer to make a digital copy of a program I paid to watch. You cannot call the decline in television quality/cancellation of good shows the fault of the Internet.
